Wrapped in the remains of a boa constrictor, teeming with filth and moss—that which the swamp provides shall never be returned.
Her organs melted and fused into a burning mass.
Something, or someone, grew within her, its bones protruding, limbs reaching for freedom from the prison of flesh.

Ornamented of bone and blood, with teeth formed of the serpent. The result of one whose humanity has long been lost to rage and revenge.
Her charred dreads could not cover the painful, serum-filled blisters on her head.
The mark of power carved into her forehead allowed her to access unnatural abilities, but with it came a repulsive transformation.

The serum turned her flesh into hardened thorns.
The ferocity of her claw was given new life by the tumorous growth that formed from it.

Her head crawled with pain as sprouts twisted within, brightening her with leafy hues.
Vegetation grew deep within her husk, tearing her apart in a beautiful red and green glow.
A sticky fluid oozed from her pores as her claw felt more like a merciless clamp.
A deep outrage surged and stiffened her body, transforming her limbs into a hard, crust.
Damp soil grumbled, and roots sprung from the ground.
Her bond with nature empowered her to tear her assailants apart.

A crown crafted for a very special anniversary.
“Thank you for supporting & inspiring us along the years!” —The Dead by Daylight Team
A rotting garland of moss spread on the twisted and fractured claw.
The smell alone was nearly enough to kill.
Her face resembled a fish, her body almost human… a true horror from the depths.
Just as capable of rending flesh on land as they are at sea.
